## 11. Risk register + deliberate breathing room (for the executor bot)

| Risk | Mitigation / compromise the bot is allowed to make |
|---|---|
| Arc testnet flaky (v0.7.2 just shipped) | Network-agnostic settlement → swap to Base Sepolia or another Gateway testnet via config. Demo still settles. |
| Gateway-on-Arc behaves differently than the 11 mainnet chains | Meter decoupled from backend → fall back to **direct x402 settlement** without touching accrual logic. |
| ERC-8004 slashing too complex by deadline | Deploy registry + bond; ship **semi-manual/simple** slash on resolve; label "beta." Don't block spine. |
| Proof-of-flow too heavy | Ship heartbeat pause/resume; mark refund logic "beta." |
| OSS connector integration drags | Make **one** truly live; others **stubbed with honest status**, never faked. |
| LLM agent cost (your $5) | Cheap model, hard token caps, cache, per-agent budget. Throttle the always-on buyer. |
| Email/social login issues | Reown AppKit primary; **wallet-only as fallback** so connect never fully breaks. |
| Time crunch | The spine (Days 1–3) is the non-negotiable; everything Day 4+ is additive and can be trimmed to honest "roadmap" without faking. |

> **Standing instruction to the bot:** never fake data or fake a working integration to hit a deadline. A clearly-labeled "beta/roadmap" state always beats a fake. Prefer shipping the spine solid over shipping breadth broken.

